Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle at neck join. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine orange-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.200, 29). Name Ieron. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0145.10.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0874)
